"""
SAP HR Monthly Lineage Generator - CORRECTED
Run this script to create lineage event for SAP HR transformation
"""

import json
import datetime
from notebookutils import mssparkutils

print("="*80)
print("SAP HR MONTHLY LINEAGE GENERATION")
print("="*80)

# ============================================================================
# STEP 1: Define Paths - CORRECTED CONTAINER NAME!
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 1: Defining file paths...")

STORAGE_ACCOUNT = "pinsstodwdevuksl92q7c"

# CORRECTED: Container is "odw-config", not "ls-storage"
SOURCE_SCHEMA_PATH = f"abfss://odw-config@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net/standardised_table_definitions/saphr/sap_hr_history_monthly.json"

TARGET_SCHEMA_PATH = f"abfss://odw-config@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net/harmonised_table_definitions/saphr/load_sap_hr_monthly.json"

# Events storage path
EVENTS_PATH = f"abfss://openlineage-events@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net"

# Namespace (your Synapse workspace)
NAMESPACE = "mssql://pins-synw-odw-dev-uks.sql.azuresynapse.net"

print("‚úÖ Paths defined")
print(f"   Container: odw-config")
print(f"   Source: standardised_table_definitions/saphr/sap_hr_history_monthly.json")
print(f"   Target: harmonised_table_definitions/saphr/load_sap_hr_monthly.json")

# ============================================================================
# STEP 2: Load Schema Files
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 2: Loading schema files...")

# Load source schema
try:
    source_content = mssparkutils.fs.head(SOURCE_SCHEMA_PATH, 100000)
    source_schema = json.loads(source_content)
    source_columns = len(source_schema.get('fields', []))
    print(f"‚úÖ Source schema loaded: {source_columns} columns")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"‚ùå ERROR loading source schema: {e}")
    print(f"   Check file exists at: {SOURCE_SCHEMA_PATH}")
    source_schema = None
    raise

# Load target schema
try:
    target_content = mssparkutils.fs.head(TARGET_SCHEMA_PATH, 100000)
    target_schema = json.loads(target_content)
    target_columns = len(target_schema.get('fields', []))
    print(f"‚úÖ Target schema loaded: {target_columns} columns")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"‚ùå ERROR loading target schema: {e}")
    print(f"   Check file exists at: {TARGET_SCHEMA_PATH}")
    target_schema = None
    raise

# ============================================================================
# STEP 3: Build OpenLineage Event
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 3: Building OpenLineage event...")

# Generate unique run ID
run_id = f"load_sap_hr_monthly-{datetime.datetime.utcnow().strftime('%Y%m%d%H%M%S')}"
print(f"   Run ID: {run_id}")

# Build INPUT dataset (source table)
input_dataset = {
    "namespace": NAMESPACE,
    "name": "odw_standardised_db.sap_hr_history_monthly"
}

# Add source schema if available
if source_schema:
    input_dataset["facets"] = {
        "schema": {
            "fields": [
                {
                    "name": field.get("name"),
                    "type": field.get("type", "string")
                }
                for field in source_schema.get("fields", [])
            ]
        }
    }

# Build OUTPUT dataset (target table)
output_dataset = {
    "namespace": NAMESPACE,
    "name": "odw_harmonised_db.load_sap_hr_monthly"
}

# Add target schema if available
if target_schema:
    output_dataset["facets"] = {
        "schema": {
            "fields": [
                {
                    "name": field.get("name"),
                    "type": field.get("type", "STRING")
                }
                for field in target_schema.get("fields", [])
            ]
        }
    }

# Create complete OpenLineage event
event = {
    "eventType": "COMPLETE",
    "eventTime": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + "Z",
    "producer": "sap-hr-lineage-generator",
    "job": {
        "namespace": NAMESPACE,
        "name": "load_sap_hr_monthly",
        "facets": {
            "documentation": {
                "description": "SAP HR monthly data transformation from standardised to harmonised layer"
            }
        }
    },
    "run": {
        "runId": run_id
    },
    "inputs": [input_dataset],
    "outputs": [output_dataset]
}

print("‚úÖ Event structure created")
print(f"   Input: odw_standardised_db.sap_hr_history_monthly")
print(f"   Output: odw_harmonised_db.load_sap_hr_monthly")

# ============================================================================
# STEP 4: Write Event to Storage
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 4: Writing event to blob storage...")

# Create dated folder path
now = datetime.datetime.utcnow()
year, month, day = now.strftime("%Y,%m,%d").split(',')
filename = f"y={year}/m={month}/d={day}/{run_id}.json"
full_path = f"{EVENTS_PATH}/{filename}"

print(f"   Writing to: {filename}")

try:
    # Write event as JSON
    mssparkutils.fs.put(full_path, json.dumps(event, indent=2), True)
    print(f"‚úÖ Event written successfully!")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"‚ùå ERROR writing event: {e}")
    raise

# ============================================================================
# STEP 5: Verify Event Was Created
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 5: Verifying event file...")

try:
    # List files in today's folder
    folder_path = f"{EVENTS_PATH}/y={year}/m={month}/d={day}/"
    files = mssparkutils.fs.ls(folder_path)
    
    # Find our event
    our_event = [f for f in files if run_id in f.name]
    
    if our_event:
        print(f"‚úÖ Event file verified!")
        print(f"   File name: {our_event[0].name}")
        print(f"   File size: {our_event[0].size} bytes")
    else:
        print(f"‚ö†Ô∏è  Event file not found immediately (may need a moment)")
        
except Exception as e:
    print(f"‚ö†Ô∏è  Could not verify (file may still exist): {e}")

# ============================================================================
# SUMMARY
# ============================================================================
print("\n" + "="*80)
print("LINEAGE EVENT GENERATION COMPLETE!")
print("="*80)

print(f"""
‚úÖ What happened:
   1. Loaded schemas from odw-config container
   2. Created OpenLineage event with column-level metadata
   3. Wrote event to: {filename}

üìã Event Details:
   ‚Ä¢ Source: odw_standardised_db.sap_hr_history_monthly ({source_columns} columns)
   ‚Ä¢ Target: odw_harmonised_db.load_sap_hr_monthly ({target_columns} columns)
   ‚Ä¢ Job Name: load_sap_hr_monthly
   ‚Ä¢ Run ID: {run_id}

üîÑ Next Steps:
   1. Parser function will automatically pick up this event (5-10 minutes)
   2. Parser will transform it to Purview format
   3. Parser will upload to Purview
   4. Lineage will appear in Purview!

üîç Check Purview:
   1. Go to: https://web.purview.azure.com
   2. Search for: "load_sap_hr_monthly"
   3. Click on the table asset
   4. Go to "Lineage" tab
   5. You should see: sap_hr_history_monthly ‚Üí load_sap_hr_monthly

‚è±Ô∏è  Wait 5-10 minutes for parser to process this event
""")

print("="*80)

"""
SAP HR Monthly Lineage Generator - FINAL CORRECTED VERSION
Uses EXACT qualified names from Purview

import json
import datetime
from notebookutils import mssparkutils

print("="*80)
print("SAP HR MONTHLY LINEAGE GENERATION - FINAL")
print("="*80)

# ============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION - CORRECTED QUALIFIED NAMES!
# ============================================================================
STORAGE_ACCOUNT = "pinsstodwdevuksl92q7c"

# Schema file paths
SOURCE_SCHEMA_PATH = f"abfss://odw-config@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net/standardised_table_definitions/saphr/sap_hr_history_monthly.json"
TARGET_SCHEMA_PATH = f"abfss://odw-config@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net/harmonised_table_definitions/saphr/load_sap_hr_monthly.json"

TARGET_QUALIFIED_NAME = "mssql://pins-synw-odw-dev-uks-ondemand.sql.azuresynapse.net/odw_harmonised_db/dbo/load_sap_hr_monthly"

print(f"   Target QN: {TARGET_QUALIFIED_NAME}")

# Build INPUT dataset - using EXACT qualified name from Purview

    "name": SOURCE_QUALIFIED_NAME
}

# Add source schema if available
if source_schema:

                    "name": field.get("name"),
                    "type": field.get("type", "string")
                }
                for field in source_schema.get("fields", [])
            ]
        }
    }

# Build OUTPUT dataset - using EXACT qualified name from Purview
output_dataset = {

    "name": TARGET_QUALIFIED_NAME
}

# Add target schema if available
if target_schema:

        "schema": {
            "fields": [
                {
                    "name": field.get("name"),
                    "type": field.get("type", "STRING")
                }
                for field in target_schema.get("fields", [])
            ]
        }
    }

# Create complete OpenLineage event
event = {

    "job": {
        "namespace": JOB_NAMESPACE,
        "name": "load_sap_hr_monthly",
        "facets": {
            "documentation": {
                "description": "SAP HR monthly data transformation from standardised to harmonised layer"
            }
        }
    },
    "run": {
        "runId": run_id
    },
    "inputs": [input_dataset],
    "outputs": [output_dataset]
}

print("‚úÖ Event created with correct qualified names!")

# ============================================================================
# STEP 3: Write Event to Storage
# ============================================================================
print("\nStep 3: Writing event to blob storage...")

now = datetime.datetime.utcnow()
year, month, day = now.strftime("%Y,%m,%d").split(',')
filename = f"y={year}/m={month}/d={day}/{run_id}.json"
full_path = f"{EVENTS_PATH}/{filename}"

print(f"   Writing to: {filename}")

try:

except Exception as e:

# ============================================================================

    files = mssparkutils.fs.ls(folder_path)
    our_event = [f for f in files if run_id in f.name]
    
    if our_event:
        print(f"‚úÖ Event file verified!")
        print(f"   File name: {our_event[0].name}")

except Exception as e:

print("LINEAGE EVENT GENERATION COMPLETE!")
print("="*80)

print(f"""
‚úÖ Event Created with CORRECT Qualified Names:

   Target: {TARGET_QUALIFIED_NAME}

üîÑ What Happens Next:

   2. Parser reads the qualified names
   3. Parser matches EXISTING assets in Purview
   4. Parser creates lineage relationship
   5. Lineage appears in Purview!

üîç Check Purview (after 5-10 minutes):
   1. Go to: https://web.purview.azure.com
   2. Search for: "load_sap_hr_monthly"
   3. Click on the table
   4. Go to "Lineage" tab
   5. You should now see: sap_hr_history_monthly ‚Üí load_sap_hr_monthly

üí° Key Fix Applied:
   ‚úÖ Using correct server name: pins-synw-odw-dev-uks-ondemand
   ‚úÖ Using correct format: database/dbo/table
   ‚úÖ Matching exact Purview qualified names

‚è±Ô∏è  Wait 5-10 minutes and check Purview lineage!
""")

print("="*80)

import requests
from azure.identity import DefaultAzureCredential

credential = DefaultAzureCredential()
token = credential.get_token("https://purview.azure.net/.default")

PURVIEW_ACCOUNT = "pins-pview"
base_url = f"https://{PURVIEW_ACCOUNT}.purview.azure.com"

headers = {
    "Authorization": f"Bearer {token.token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
}

# Search for recently created entities
search_url = f"{base_url}/catalog/api/search/query"
search_body = {
    "keywords": "load_sap_hr_monthly",
    "limit": 20
}

response = requests.post(search_url, headers=headers, json=search_body)

if response.status_code == 200:
    results = response.json()
    
    print("="*80)
    print("ALL ASSETS WITH 'load_sap_hr_monthly' IN NAME:")
    print("="*80)
    
    for item in results.get("value", []):
        print(f"\nüìã Asset: {item.get('name')}")
        print(f"   Type: {item.get('entityType')}")
        print(f"   Qualified Name: {item.get('qualifiedName')}")
        print(f"   ID: {item.get('id')}")
        
    print(f"\n{'='*80}")
    print(f"Total found: {len(results.get('value', []))}")
else:
    print(f"Error: {response.status_code}")
    print(response.text)
